**tsconfig.json configures TypeScript compiler for ES2022 Node.js module compilation with strict type-checking and source map generation.**

## Compiler Target Configuration

`target: "ES2022"` specifies ECMAScript 2022 as compilation target, enabling top-level await, class fields, and private methods in emitted JavaScript.

`lib: ["ES2022"]` restricts TypeScript to ES2022 standard library type definitions, preventing usage of newer APIs not available in Node.js ≥18.0.0.

## Module System

`module: "NodeNext"` and `moduleResolution: "NodeNext"` enable Node.js native ESM support with `.js` extension requirements in import statements and package.json `"type": "module"` detection.

`esModuleInterop: true` enables CommonJS/ESM interop via synthetic default imports for libraries without default exports.

`resolveJsonModule: true` allows importing `.json` files as modules (used for package.json metadata in `src/integration/generate.ts` and version detection).

`isolatedModules: true` enforces single-file transpilation compatibility required by `tsx` dev runner and Vite-based build tools.

## Build Paths

`rootDir: "src"` designates `src/` as compilation root, preserving directory structure in output.

`outDir: "dist"` emits compiled JavaScript to `dist/` directory (referenced by `package.json` bin entries `dist/cli/index.js`).

`include: ["src/**/*"]` compiles all TypeScript files under `src/`.

`exclude: ["node_modules", "dist"]` prevents compilation of dependencies and emitted output.

## Type Declaration Generation

`declaration: true` emits `.d.ts` type declaration files alongside compiled `.js` files for API consumers.

`declarationMap: true` generates `.d.ts.map` files enabling IDE jump-to-source navigation from compiled declarations to original TypeScript source.

`sourceMap: true` generates `.js.map` files for debugging compiled code with source-level stack traces.

## Type Safety

`strict: true` enables all strict type-checking options (strictNullChecks, strictFunctionTypes, strictBindCallApply, strictPropertyInitialization, noImplicitThis, alwaysStrict, noImplicitAny, noImplicitReturns, noFallthroughCasesInSwitch).

`forceConsistentCasingInFileNames: true` prevents cross-platform issues from case-insensitive filesystems treating `Logger.ts` and `logger.ts` as identical.

`skipLibCheck: true` skips type-checking of `.d.ts` files in `node_modules/` to reduce compilation time (necessary with 40+ dependencies including `@anthropic-ai/claude-code`, `fast-glob`, `zod`).

## Integration with Build Pipeline

Referenced by `npm run build` in package.json, which executes `tsc` without arguments (reads tsconfig.json by default).

Consumed by `tsx watch src/cli/index.ts` dev mode (npm run dev) for hot-reload type-checking.

Used by npm prepublishOnly hook to compile src/ → dist/ before tarball creation for registry publishing.